ENTRY       EC 1.14.15.13               Enzyme
NAME        pulcherriminic acid synthase;
            cyclo-L-leucyl-L-leucyl dipeptide oxidase;
            CYP134A1;
            CypX (ambiguous)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With reduced iron-sulfur protein as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into the other donor
SYSNAME     cyclo(L-leucyl-L-leucyl),reduced-ferredoxin:oxygen oxidoreductase (N-hydroxylating,aromatizing)
REACTION    cyclo(L-leucyl-L-leucyl) + 6 reduced ferredoxin + 3 O2 = pulcherriminic acid + 6 oxidized ferredoxin + 4 H2O [RN:R10322]
ALL_REAC    R10322
SUBSTRATE   cyclo(L-leucyl-L-leucyl) [CPD:C20514];
            reduced ferredoxin [CPD:C00138];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     pulcherriminic acid [CPD:C20515];
            oxidized ferredoxin [CPD:C00139];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     A heme-thiolate (P-450) enzyme from the bacterium Bacillus subtilis. The order of events during the overall reaction is unknown. Pulcherrimic acid spontaneously forms an iron chelate with Fe(3+) to form the red pigment pulcherrimin [2].
